    <body>
      <entry xml:id="entry_qæznyg" xml:lang="os" abv:completeness="incomplete">
        <form type="lemma" xml:lang="os-x-iron"><orth>qæznyg</orth><form type="variant"
              ><orth>qæzdyg</orth></form></form>
        <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>ǧæzdug</orth></form>
        <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
            <q>богатый</q>
          </abv:tr></sense>
        <exampleGrp xmlns="http://ossetic-studies.org/ns/abaevdict">
          <example>
            <quote xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Axmæt... tyng qæzdyg cardī, fos, xæzna —
              bīræ</quote>
            <tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Ахмат жил очень богато, скота, сокровищ (у него
                было) много</q>
            </tr>
            <bibl xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/>
              <biblScope>33</biblScope></bibl>
          </example>
          <example>
            <quote xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">xæʒar fæqæzdyg</quote>
            <tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">дом разбогател</q>
            </tr>
            <bibl xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/>
              <biblScope>85</biblScope></bibl>
          </example>
          <example>
            <quote xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">qæzdyg cardæj cærync G˳yrʒystony
              fællojgænǵytæ</quote>
            <tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">богатой жизнью живут трудящиеся Грузии</q>
            </tr>
            <bibl xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><ref type="bibl" target="#src_F."/>
              <biblScope>1956 II 6</biblScope></bibl>
          </example>
          <example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
            <usg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><lang/></usg>
            <quote xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">ærlæwwioncæ ǧæzdug fusunmæ</quote>
            <tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">они останавливались у богатого хозяина</q>
            </tr>
            <bibl xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Bes."/>
              <biblScope>104</biblScope></bibl>
          </example>
        </exampleGrp>
        <re>
          <form type="lemma"><orth>qæzdydag</orth></form>
          <sense><tr xmlns="http://ossetic-studies.org/ns/abaevdict" xml:lang="ru">
              <q xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">богатство</q>
            </tr></sense>
          <note type="comment"> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Марк"/>
              <biblScope><hi rendition="#rend_italic">4</hi> 19</biblScope></bibl>)</note>
        </re>
        <etym xml:lang="ru">Конечный <m xml:lang="os-x-iron">-yg</m><m xml:lang="os-x-digor"
          >-ug</m>— суффикс, как в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_būznyg"/> и др. Ср.
            <?oxy_comment_start author="julie" timestamp="20220412T225142+0300" comment="NB"?><ref
            type="xr" target="">д. gæzdæ- 'богатство’</ref><?oxy_comment_end?>, как
            <?oxy_comment_start author="julie" timestamp="20220412T225242+0300" comment="NB"?><ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_bæz-"><w>bæzdæ</w> (вместо <w>bæznæ</w>)
            <q>толщина</q></ref><?oxy_comment_end?>.<hi rendition="#rend_superscript">1</hi>
          <note type="footnote">В <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="">словаре языков и наречий
                Афганистана Шахи Абдуллы Бадахши</ref>
              <biblScope>(Кабул, 1960)</biblScope></bibl> дается, между прочим, форма <mentioned
              xml:lang="sgy"><lang/>
              <w>yåzd</w>
              <note type="bibl">(<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_AO"><hi
                      rendition="#rend_smallcaps">Morgenstierne</hi>, АО</ref>
                  <biblScope>1966 XXX 182</biblScope></bibl>)</note></mentioned>. Ср. колебание
              <mentioned xml:lang="sla"><w>grozd-</w> || <w>grozn-</w>
              <gloss><q>гроздь</q></gloss></mentioned> в славянском. <mentioned xml:lang="zkh"><lang/>
              <w>γazdak</w></mentioned> также говорит о параллельном существовании форм <w>gazn-</w>
            и <w>gazd-</w>.</note> Основа <w xml:lang="os-x-iron">qæzn-</w><w xml:lang="os-x-digor"
            >ǧæzn-</w> возводится к <lang>иран.</lang>
          <w type="rec">gazna-</w> || <w type="rec">ganza-</w>. Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/>
            <w>γanz</w>
            <note type="bibl">(<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Lorimer"/></bibl>)</note>,
              <w>γanj</w>
            <note type="comment">(<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="">Андреев. Таджики долины Хуф, вып.
                  II.</ref>
                <biblScope>Сталинабад, 1958, стр. 16</biblScope></bibl>)</note></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/>
            <w>yånz</w>
            <gloss><q>сокровище</q>, <q>хранилище</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
            <w type="rec">γazn-</w>, <w type="rec">γanz-</w>
            <gloss><q>сокровище</q>, <q>богатство</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xpr"><lang/>
            <w>gazn-</w>
            <gloss>id.</gloss>, <w>gazn-bar</w>
            <gloss><q>казначей</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/>
            <w type="rec">ganza-bara-</w> id. <note type="bibl">(<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                  target="#ref_Asia_Major"><hi rendition="#rend_smallcaps">Gershevitch</hi>, Asia
                  Major</ref>
                <biblScope>1951, стр. 143, 144</biblScope></bibl>)</note></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="zkh"><lang/>
            <w>γazdak</w>
            <gloss><q>богатый</q></gloss>
            <note type="bibl">(<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Henning._Khwar."/>
                <biblScope>14</biblScope></bibl>)</note></mentioned>. Из иранского слово вошло в
          другие индоевропейские языки (санскрит, армянский, греческий), а также в семитические
              (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Mayrhofer"/>
            <biblScope>I 315</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target=""><hi
                rendition="#rend_smallcaps">Дандамаев</hi>, Gedenkschrift für W. Brandenstein</ref>,
              <biblScope>Innsbruck, 1968, стр. 239</biblScope></bibl>). Из осетинского идет,
          возможно, <mentioned xml:lang="hu"><lang/>
            <w>kazdag</w>, <w>gazdag</w>
            <gloss><q>богатый</q></gloss></mentioned>. <mentioned xml:lang="hu"><lang>Венг.</lang>
            <w>gazda</w>
            <gloss><q>хозяин</q>, <q>владелец</q></gloss></mentioned> примыкает к
            <?oxy_comment_start author="julie" timestamp="20220412T225142+0300" comment="NB"?><ref
            type="xr" target="">д. gæzdæ- 'богатство’</ref><?oxy_comment_end?>; отсюда <mentioned
            xml:lang="sr" extralang="cs"><lang/>
            <w>gazda</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="uk"
              ><?oxy_comment_start author="julie" timestamp="20220412T231048+0300" comment="NB"?><lang>укр.
              (зап.)</lang><?oxy_comment_end?>
            <w>газда</w>
            <gloss><q>хозяин</q></gloss></mentioned>. Некоторые выводят <mentioned xml:lang="hu"
              ><lang>Венг.</lang>
            <w>gazda</w></mentioned> из <lang>слав,</lang>
          <w>gospoda</w>
          <note type="bibl">(<bibl><ref type="bibl" target=""><hi rendition="#rend_smallcaps"
                  >Меillеt</hi>. Le slave commun.</ref>
              <biblScope>Ed. 2. Paris, 1934, § 584</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                target="">Machek. Etym. slovník.</ref>
              <biblScope>Praha, 1957, стр. 116</biblScope></bibl>, и др.)</note>.<lb/><bibl><ref
              type="bibl" target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"/>
            <biblScope>15</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl"
              target="#ref_Bailey._Asica._Suppl.">Asica. Suppl.</ref>
            <biblScope>206</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_KSz."><hi
                rendition="#rend_smallcaps">Munkácsi</hi>, KSz.</ref>
            <biblScope>I 213, V 317, IV 380</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
              target="#ref_Sköld._Oss."/>
            <biblScope>22</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
      </entry>
